title: For Sale:  Inland M1 Carbine-1943
postcontent:
This is WWII era (August 1943) US Carbine Cal. 30 M1. A piece of history.

Markings;
Reciever,  INLAND DIV 614829

Barrel; 
INLAND MFG. Div. General Motors 8-43

Breach;
US CARBINE CAL. 30 M1

Side of Breach;
MEREX SAV GA (This is an importer's stamp. A lot of the WWII weapons were exported to allied countries after the war and then reimported and sold. Merex corp has an interesting history of it's own. Widely believed to be a CIA front company it was involved heavily in the Iran/Contra arms scandal. Google Merex for more info.)

More photos can be seen here; http://photobucket.com/inland_m1_carbine . (Copy and paste to your browser.)

The Carbine is in overall good condition as can be seen in the photos. I have fired it quite a bit and it functions well and is fun to shoot. 
The bore is dark(it looks like it has been fired with corrosive primers and not cleaned well.) The lands a grooves are crisp; however.

Included with the rifle are 3 15 round magazines and 1 30 round magazine and 100 rounds of ammunition.

I have retired and am selling some of my stuff.

I am asking $550.00 OBO
